D38 — R9 Clark short-tree volume SIGFPE on real FIA stands (all variants; SN worst).
The Clark taper terms (1-h/totHt)**p in r9ht/r9dib/r9cuft legitimately go SUBNORMAL
for short trees (totHt just > the 17.3 ft reference) and NaN for totHt < 17.3 ft.
The build traps underflow+denormal+invalid, so it ABORTS (SIGFPE, no .sum) on valid
inventory. Two-part fix, both matching the independent Julia port (src/engine/
r9clark_vol.jl) and verified BYTE-IDENTICAL on non-crash stands:

(1) BUILD FLAG (bin/makefile_Xbuild): drop underflow,denormal from -ffpe-trap. Gradual
    underflow to a denormal is well-defined IEEE; the port does not trap it either.
    Denormals now flow with zero output change; fixes every denormal crash site.
(2) SOURCE (volume/NVEL/r9clark.f): guard the remaining invalid-op (negative base,
    totHt<17.3) in r9ht and r9dib — Y=0 is the correct limit (the 17.3 ft profile term
    vanishes), mirroring the guard r9cuft already has near line 1015.

Validation: 8/8 sampled crashers + 162/162 second-wave crashers now emit .sum; cycle-0
volume bit-exact vs the Julia port; 40/40 normal stands byte-identical patched-vs-pristine.

=== build flag ===
--- a/bin/makefile_Xbuild : -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,underflow,overflow,denormal
+++ b/bin/makefile_Xbuild : -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,overflow

